##National multi-district issued "pass" to limit the number of times in and out, experts: There is a legal basis, should pay attention to standards

REPORTER: Zhao Mengwangchang (intern reporter)

In the early morning of February 11,2020, Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and control headquarters circular No. 12 was issued, decided to implement the city-wide closed management of all residential areas from today.

Interface news through combing found that on February 3, Hangzhou overnight emergency issued a city-wide closed-type management notice, since then closed-type management in the country to follow.

With the increase of epidemic prevention and control measures, Jiangsu, Tianjin, Fujian, Beijing, Chongqing, Guangdong and other provinces and cities have implemented closed management. These closed management of the community in and out of temperature, to distribute "pass" way, strict control of the daily or weekly number of people into the community and the number of times.

Some communities in places such as Shenzhen have issued "passes" , while those in Chongqing, Kunming, Harbin and Huangshan City have restricted the number of people allowed in and out of their homes under closed management, requiring residents to make regular purchases, according to public information. There were no confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia in a community in Huangshan City, but the rule was that only one person in the family, apart from those required to work, could get a pass and travel for two hours every two days, no deliveries, either. A small community in Nantong City, Sichuan Province, has issued a one-day and two-day travel regulations.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Is there a legal basis for a gated community? Zhao Liangshan, a senior partner of Shaanxi Hengda Law Firm and a well-known public interest lawyer, told interface news that measures such as the closure of residential areas were special measures taken by the local government during the special period of the epidemic, in order to ensure public health safety and public health, it is necessary to sacrifice part of personal interests, adhere to the principle of public collective interests over personal interests, and so on.

Article forty-two of the Law on the prevention and Control of infectious diseases stipulates that in the event of an outbreak or epidemic of an infectious disease, local Government of the People's Republic of China at or above the county level shall immediately organize forces to carry out prevention and control in accordance with the preventive and control plans, and cut off the means of transmission of infectious diseases if necessary, the following emergency measures may be taken and announced upon the decision of the Government of the People's Republic of China at the next higher level: (1) restriction or suspension of activities in markets, cinemas and theatres or other gatherings of people; (2) suspension of work, business or classes; (3) to seal up or seal up public drinking water sources, food and related articles that are polluted by Infectious Disease Pathogens; (4) to control or put to death wild animals, livestock and poultry that are infected with infectious diseases; and (5) to seal up places that may cause the spread of infectious diseases. When a higher Government of the People's Republic of China receives a report from a lower Government of the People's Republic of China on the adoption of the urgent measures listed in the preceding paragraph, it shall make an immediate decision. The lifting of emergency measures shall be decided and announced by the organ that originally decided the matter.

Zhao said the law gives the local government the power to take measures to cut off the spread of infectious diseases, such as the closure of residential areas. In the implementation, by the implementation of residential property. If the implementation of residential property is not effective, resulting in COVID-19, in accordance with the "law on public security management penalties, " the person in charge of residential property security penalties.

Mao Shoulong, a professor at the School of Public Administration at Renmin University of China, said: "The new coronavirus is too fierce, the community closed management, is a good way to cut off the virus in the community, strengthen community management is not wrong, but the specific measures of the closed community is worth considering, " he said, scanning Code into the community, temperature measures are no problem, but the odd and even number restrictions in and out, curfews and other measures are not professional prevention and control.

In Mao Shoulong's view, gated community management refers to the management of transient populations, which should be aimed at early detection, early isolation and the reduction of visits to each other, rather than restricting access.

Although it is legal for the government or property company to close the residential area, Zhao Liangshan reminded the government that when issuing similar decisions and orders, it should pay attention to the legality, reasonableness and necessity of the decisions and orders issued, its power can not be extended indefinitely. "For example, decisions and orders should be made in strict accordance with the provisions of the administrative compulsory law, and the procedures should be lawful. According to current clinical judgment, the COVID-19 is latent in the human body for 7 to 14 days, and each person needs to isolate himself for about 14 days, and the government can not extend the isolation for one month or indefinitely when issuing decisions or orders."

Mao Shoulong suggested that communities in the affected areas, or those with confirmed cases, should be closely monitored, closed management, and if suspected patients are found, quarantine by the CDC and hospitals. Or Epidemiological Investigation has not been completed in the community, should be completely closed to do a good investigation, and then to conduct general closed management, such as security guard, in and out of body temperature. If someone in the community closed management and delay the illness, the immediate manager should be responsible.

Liu Peng, a professor at the School of Public Administration at Renmin University in Beijing, said local governments should have a basis for upgrading prevention and control measures and should not overreact. Based on the number of confirmed cases or confirmed diagnosis, the local government should issue relevant content to remind the public, otherwise not only cause inconvenience to life, but also may lead to psychological panic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In addition to closed communities, some units also through the epidemic, such as the form of meetings to fight the epidemic. Liu Peng reminded that prevention and control should be neither one size fits all, nor simple, nor formalism.
